Prince William is due to take two weeks’ paid paternity leave following the birth of his first child before returning to work as an RAF pilot.

The Duke has made it clear that he is not expecting special treatment from military bosses despite the birth of his first child being in the public spotlight.

He will take a fortnight of statutory paternity leave and will be paid £136.78 a week.

