It is understood that the Duke will then return to work at RAF Valley in Anglesey, Wales, where he will resume his normal shift pattern.

Despite his sense of duty, the journey could prove a lonely one for the Duke, as his wife and child will not be making the journey to Wales. 

Only last month, it was feared that William might miss the birth due to remaining on standby as a pilot while his wife went into labour. 

